<div id="review_1642597977" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1642597977" />
    <a title="John Eliot" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32482032-john-eliot"><img alt="John Eliot" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1403469614p2/32482032.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1642597977?book_show_action=true">May 19, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="John Eliot" class="user" itemprop="url" name="John Eliot" href="/user/show/32482032-john-eliot">John Eliot</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1642597977" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10445546497344710646">The edition I have of this book was republished over 50 times between 1929 and 1974. The popularity quite incredible. It&apos;s weakness is probably is that it was first published in 1929. It hasn&apos;t always dated as well as other novels that were published long ago. At times it is twee. On the positive side it is very well written, at times stunningly well written. The story of a concert party in 1929 is quite fascinating in this day when they don&apos;t exist and all forms of entertainment are on the tele</span>
  <span id="freeText10445546497344710646" style="display:none">The edition I have of this book was republished over 50 times between 1929 and 1974. The popularity quite incredible. It's weakness is probably is that it was first published in 1929. It hasn't always dated as well as other novels that were published long ago. At times it is twee. On the positive side it is very well written, at times stunningly well written. The story of a concert party in 1929 is quite fascinating in this day when they don't exist and all forms of entertainment are on the television. There are parts of the novel which are very Sillitoe as he writes about terraced house working class Yorkshire. I think if you were new to Priestley I'd read something by him that was more up to date.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10445546497344710646" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


