<div id="review_140307895" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/140307895" />
    <a title="Shu Chadwick" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2550212-shu-chadwick"><img alt="Shu Chadwick" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/140307895?book_show_action=true">Jan 12, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shu Chadwick" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shu Chadwick" href="/user/show/2550212-shu-chadwick">Shu Chadwick</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer140307895" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7233426003223079385">One of my top ten all time favourite books -- the story of a rag-tag Concert Party (theatrical variety show) travelling the UK in the late 1920s. Simply wonderful -- filled with humanity, humour, pathos and other delights. My reading group -- which is very close to my heart and has been going for nearly 30 years -- read this book 20+ years ago and adopted the name The Good Companions. Re-reading it for the umpteenth time.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

